    <h2>About Nintendo</h2>
    <p>
      Nintendo was founded in 1889 as Nintendo Koppai by craftsman Fusajiro Yamauchi 
      and originally produced handmade hanafuda playing cards. After venturing into 
      various lines of business during the 1960s and acquiring legal status as a public 
      company, Nintendo distributed its first console, the Color TV-Game, in 1977. It 
      gained international recognition with the release of Donkey Kong in 1981 and the 
      Nintendo Entertainment System and Super Mario Bros. in 1985.
    </p>
    </section>
